reviews.title: 5.0 out of 5 stars 9.5/10
reviews.author: Dylan
reviews.content: Very satisfied with the quality of these earbuds. The sound is fantastic, dynamic sound with satisfying bass. The active noise canceling works surprisingly well for in ear buds. Just the ANC alone with no audio will significantly reduce background noise. There is also an option for ambient noise to be played which i like to use when reading or sleeping.If you have the ANC on & are playing music you will not hear any background noise short of a jackhammer next to your ears.As to be expected from in ear buds, but still worth mentioning, there is virtually zero noise leak from these. People around you will not be able to hear what you're playing even if it's loud.I bought these mainly to use at the gym. One of my main concerns was that these would fall out easily while I'm workout out or running, as I've had that issue with other ear buds. I have not had that issue at all, these fit very securely in the ear and do not fall out easily at all, while still being very comfortable. There is a little ridge that will slide into the groove above your ear canal that makes them very secure.Battery life is great and they charge quickly. They come with a C-to-C charging cord that will charge the case very rapidly.My only minor complaint is that they don't go quite as loud as I would like them to, but I'm someone who always listens to my music very loudly. They are by no means quiet earbuds and this should only dissuade you if you're someone looking for earbuds capable of going extremely loud.Really for this price they are fantastic. Nothing I've purchased in this price range previously comes close.
reviews.timestamp: Reviewed in the United States September 6, 2024

reviews.title: 5.0 out of 5 stars No Way

As soon as I opened the case, my phone woke up and was like, "Eeeey, these yours?" And I was off to the races.3) Feature rich as all getout. Disclaimer. I am not somebody that likes very feature rich things. I like my audio devices to play audio. Nothing more. These changed my mind completely. It works so seamlessly with the phone it feels like an expansion pack or something. Answering calls is easy and has incredible mic quality. Not sure how. Playing, pausing, and playing next and previous songs all uses one touch surface and it's way easier than expected.4) My absolute favorite thing about these. Audio quality. I'm absolutely blown away by how good these sound. I didn't think it was possible to get such huge sound out of earbuds. These lil things are the size of a roided out bean and they absolutely dominate my entire skull. Most people are going to be like "Yo the bass is fire. Riz and bruh and other sounds," but it's so much more than that. They deliver rich and clean audio across all frequencies. Yes, bass included. Very very f****** included. I listen to a lot of metal, which can be really demanding of speakers. The genre often includes a wide range of audio input simultaneously. These handle anything you throw at them no problem.In short, buy these. Go. Do it. Begone.

reviews.title: 4.0 out of 5 stars Good buds!
reviews.author: David D
reviews.content: I recently purchased the SAMSUNG Galaxy Buds FE True Wireless Bluetooth Earbuds in the Graphite color and I have been extremely impressed with their performance. As someone who is always on the go and constantly listening to music or podcasts, having a reliable and comfortable pair of earbuds is essential for me. The Galaxy Buds FE have exceeded my expectations in both of these areas.First and foremost, the comfort and secure fit of these earbuds is top-notch. The wing-tip design ensures that they stay in place even during intense workouts or when I'm running errands. I have tried many other wireless earbuds in the past and have always struggled with finding a pair that stays in my ears comfortably. The Galaxy Buds FE have solved this problem for me and I can wear them for hours without any discomfort.The sound quality of these earbuds is also impressive. The audio is clear and crisp, with a good balance of bass and treble. I have used them for both music and phone calls and have been pleased with the sound in both scenarios. The touch controls on the earbuds are also very convenient and easy to use. I can easily pause or skip a song without having to take out my phone.One of the standout features of these earbuds is the auto switch audio. This allows me to seamlessly switch between my phone and laptop when I receive a call or want to listen to something on my computer. It's a small feature, but it has made a big difference in my daily routine.I also appreciate the built-in voice assistant feature. I can easily access my virtual assistant with just a touch of the earbud, making it convenient to make calls, send texts, or get directions without having to take out my phone.The battery life on these earbuds is also impressive. I can use them for several hours without needing to recharge, and the charging case provides additional battery life when I'm on the go. The case is also compact and easy to carry around.Overall, I highly recommend the SAMSUNG Galaxy Buds FE True Wireless Bluetooth Earbuds. They offer a comfortable and secure fit, great sound quality, and convenient features that make them a must-have for anyone looking for a reliable pair of wireless earbuds. Whether you're a music lover, fitness enthusiast, or just someone who wants a hassle-free listening experience, these earbuds are definitely worth considering.The only drawback is that the case is not wireless charging. Losing the one star.

reviews.title: 5.0 out of 5 stars Incredible Value, Samsung Delivers
reviews.author: Matt
reviews.content: Sound Quality: 8/10These don’t sound like earbuds I just dropped $75 on. They sound like premium quality, well-balanced, and capable wireless earbuds. Bass actually comes through with a satisfying low end and instrument separation is clear and natural. They’re also handle dialogue clarity very well.Comfort and Fit: 9/10These are the most comfortable wireless earbuds I’ve ever used. They feel nearly weightless, but at the same time very secure. The rubberized winged edge on each earbud hooks right into your ear without being uncomfortable over 4+ hours of use.Case Quality: 8/10The reason I needed to buy a pair of wireless earbuds is because the case for my last pair came apart at the hinge after a few drops. I’m not always easy on these things, they get tossed into backpacks and I’m bound to drop them here and there. The case for these feels pretty sturdy and secure. They’re a hard, glossy plastic and there’s a mechanism in place holding the lid up when fully open, which is satisfying. I don’t like how easily I can bend the lid backward as it seems to have quite a bit of give to it, but when closed it feels firmly clasped shut, so hopefully that’s never something I need to worry about.Battery Life: 7/10I get a solid 5+ hours of listening time out of these with noise cancelling on, and 3+ charges out of the case. They’re not going to blow your mind, but they hold their own just fine.Noise Cancelling: 8/10Really surprised at how well these block out noise for a pair of earbuds that cost less than $100. Cutting grass or walking near noisy roads won’t be an issue.I want acknowledge a big reason you may not want to buy these. If you’re an iPhone user, there is no app available to adjust EQ or add the functionality to skip or reverse - only pause, play, and noise cancelling controls as a default will be available to you. If you have a windows laptop or could use somebody else’s Android device for a few minutes, you can enable the ability to skip and reverse and play around with some other features. I myself use iPhone but don’t mind lack of app support because my fiancee has an Android, and once you set them up you’re not likely to need the app very often, if at all.

reviews.title: 3.0 out of 5 stars Better to buy new and Best with Samsung phone
reviews.author: Julie
reviews.content: This is a bit long but I feel it provides good info regarding your phone or electronic device to be paired with earbuds and purchasing new vs used earbuds. If you have questions about these topics please read!I purchased these for my boyfriend. He has a Samsung S22. I have bought him multiple types of brand new earbuds in the $70-$80 range in the past. He had to charge all those daily in order to used for 1.5 hrs while he walked. I wanted to buy him something nicer so I bought these. I chose to buy a used set in hopes that they were in great condition and maybe the box was just torn. I changed them overnight on accident (I prefer not to charge too long). Then paired then with my iPhone. I have owned several versions and pairs of iPods and Beats Pro (over the ear). So my first reaction was disappointment because the sound quality did not compare and little things didn’t work the same. For example when you take your Beats out if your ear whatever your watching stops. That is not the case with these. Also when a call comes in, I had to manually change the option to the ear bud on my phone screen vs just answering by touching my ear. However, I still gave them to my boyfriend for Easter and when he paired them with his galaxy he was prompted to add an extra app that gave him different features than I had with my Apple. Initially he was not too impressed with the sound, he expected them to be louder. The noise canceling was so good, he had to take them out to hear me talk to him. What he loved about them was the length of time he was able to go before charging the case. Remember I charged them one time, then he used them off of my original charge after sitting in the box for a few days. He wore them everyday for 5 days without charging the case. At that point he was really happy with them. Enough to overlook the sound quality since it was not what he expected. Unfortunately when he charged the case he was not able to get the Right earbud to charge. We tried different troubleshooting methods. Unfortunately none of them have worked. We will be sending them back. I don’t have experience using Apple headphones or buds with Samsung phones but I feel if I had bought these brand new, he would keep them vs buying headphones like mine. I’d rather pay an extra $50 to get new products going forward. Please air on the side of caution if you buy used or refurbished version of these ear buds. Hopefully this helps someone trying to decide between new or used and Apple/Beats products vs Other earbuds to pair with an android phone.

reviews.title: 3.0 out of 5 stars Not overly impressed
reviews.author: Amazon Cutstomer
reviews.content: I've only had these a day but there are not many reviews so I'll give my 1st impressions. I wore them for a few hours doing yard work (using my Samsung S22) and tried them with some of my favorite test tracks connected to my PC and using Amazon HD music (using Exclusive mode)The first thing that surprised me was the white case... I ordered black, and at first thought they sent the wrong ones but opened the case and the buds themselves were black. I don't like white, but whatever.Looking at the case there is not much indication of what is the front and it's a bit fiddly to open. The magnet to suck the buds into place is not very strong, so a bit fiddly to lay them in the case.I don't like wearing buds much, but these were pretty comfortable right out of the box. The insertion was not quite as deep as I like but they stayed in well while I was moving around and I did not feel the need to keep adjusting them.How do they sound:I want to emphasize these are first impressions.These have a polite sound that would probably please many people. I'm not one of them. When I got the Lypertek buds for the same price I told people "I can't believe how good a sound you can get for $100 these days". With these, I would say "They are ok, most people would like them".They are "fine" for having something playing in your ear while you do something else but they did not bring out any joy in the music for me. Nothing stood out about the sound. Ordinary comes to mind or, nothing wrong but nothing right. I'm not into 'soundstage' the the lack of one while listening to live tracks actually stood out to me.The sound is a bit congested, the instruments kind of bunched into each other. There is no 'air' around the instruments. I found myself pushing the volume louder than I normally listen to "wake them up a bit".Detail retrieval is decent, but you are not going to notice the reverb, the grind of a distorted guitar, the 'ting' of the drumsticks on a cymbal, breath sounds, etc. The overall presentation is smooth enough from low to high, with no glaring holes, or peaks. If I had to fault the frequency response it would be male voices. Just a bit in your face at times. Bass get a bit tubby if you try to push it much. In "normal" mode I found it just about right.Let's see what I can 'fix' with EQ. The EQ in the App has 9 bands, cool! But that hardly matters if there is no custom EQ option. Seriously Samsung? The Sennheiser App only has 3 bands but at least they let you set a custom EQ, name it, and save it.There are 7 presets, but none of them really gave me something I liked. But there is enough variety that most people would find something they like.I'm mixed on keeping them. The sound is good enough for what I want them for. listening to music while I do something else. They are comfortable and stay in well, but I am not impressed with the sound. It's "fine", it's "okay", and "good enough" but not impressed with the sound for the $100 price point.
reviews.timestamp: Reviewed in the United States October 21, 2023

reviews.content: I like the sound quality on these enough. the tap to pause feature is nice, but I find myself accidentally setting it off sometimes when I go to adjust or re-secure the earbuds, which unfortunately happens often since I have smaller ears. Also the double tap feature to skip songs.. I can rarely get it to work. I like these better than the beats earbuds, but the search for the perfect earbuds continues. Functionality with my phone is great. Never any issues with connections and the battery life is really good for how I use them.
reviews.timestamp: Reviewed in the United States September 5, 2024

content.product_name: SAMSUNG Galaxy Buds FE True Wireless Bluetooth Earbuds, Comfort and Secure in Ear Fit, Auto Switch Audio, Touch Control, Built-in Voice Assistant, Graphite [US Version, 1Yr Manufacturer Warranty]
